This is the story of My Senior Project:

	It began during a conversation with a dude named John Mulvey, 

who is an employee of the Loyola College Information Services department. 

John mentioned to me he had some projects that I could do, and I jumped at the chance. 

Initially my work revolved around installing a DHCP server on campus, 

but when this proved to involve no real work, I began to look for other things to do. 

John had mentioned that 'web-ifying' the existing bootp table would be beneficial, so

I began to do this. In addition to these things, I got to play around with Mulvey's 

SPARCstation 5. I was very interested in access to this machine, as it provided the

opportunity to install software and experiment. And so it began...
